response.response: 36yo, P2 + 1 - previous SVD and EMCS, 35+6 weeks, BMI 45, Rh+, with a history of postpartum hemorrhage, miscarriage at 19 weeks 6 days in 2023, gallstones, hypothyroidism on thyroxine. Admitted for hypertension and raised ALT, meeting criteria for pre-eclampsia. Considered for cholecystectomy but currently asymptomatic. Diagnosed with gestational diabetes. Fetal cardiac ultrasound showed difficulty in visualization, suggesting possible cardiac anomalies. Blood pressure elevated (175/100), asymptomatic. Management: aim for BP <140/90, monitor fetal growth, plan for delivery from 37 weeks if pre-eclampsia develops. Consider delivery at Princess Royal Hospital, discuss postpartum contraception options. Prescribe antihypertensives and continue monitoring until delivery. Follow-up postpartum for contraception.
